            "id": "4539421",
            "title": "Jabil prices $1 billion bond offering in two tranches",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://cts.businesswire.com/ct/CT?id=smartlink&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jabil.com%2F&amp;esheet=54397434&amp;newsitemid=20260115375292&amp;lan=en-US&amp;anchor=Jabil+Inc.&amp;index=1&amp;md5=1cac9a46241eb1d261505ffb508fe787\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jabil (</a><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/JBL\" title=\"Jabil Inc.\">JBL</a>) (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/JBL\" title=\"Jabil Inc.\">JBL</a></span>) said on Thursday it has priced a $1 billion debt offering, consisting of $500 million of 4.200% senior notes due 2029 and $500 million of 4.750% senior notes due 2033.</li>\n<li>The electronics manufacturing company said the offering is expected to close on January 23, 2026, subject to customary conditions.</li>\n<li>Jabil plans to use the net proceeds for general corporate purposes, including repayment of its $500 million 1.700% senior notes due 2026 at or before maturity.</li>\n<li>JBL <span>+1.01%</span> premarket to $243.8.</li>\n<li>Source: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20365704-jabil-announces-pricing-of-500-million-aggregate-principal-amount-of-4_200-percent-senior\">Press Release</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
